==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''spadu'' from Old Frisian ''spada'' from Greek ''σπάθη'' (spathi) a blade.

===Noun===
'''spade''' ([[spades]])

# A [[garden]] [[tool]] with a handle and a flat [[blade]] for [[dig]]ging. Not be be confused with a [[shovel]] which is used for moving earth or other materials.
# One of the black [[suit]]s in a deck of cards, represented by a symbol similarly to the garden tool.
# (offensive) A black person.

